---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Chowdown Strategy: March 2026" description="Data-backed strategy for Chowdown based on 30 days of real user behaviour from Umami Cloud.">

  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 pt-16 md:pt-24 pb-12">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <p class="text-amber-400 font-medium mb-2">March 2026 · 30-Day Analytics Deep Dive</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-white leading-tight">Chowdown Strategy</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-400 mt-4 leading-relaxed">
        Real data from 155 app users and 56 landing visitors. What works, what doesn't, and what to do next.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Executive Summary -->
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Executive Summary</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/20 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="text-amber-200 font-medium">🔥 ChatGPT = 59% of landing traffic. Not Google. GEO is the channel.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/20 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="text-amber-200 font-medium">📱 333 food logs, 87% mobile, 2.15 logs/user. Product-market fit confirmed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/20 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="text-amber-200 font-medium">✅ App retains well (39% bounce). Landing page leaks (71% bounce). Fix the landing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/20 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="text-amber-200 font-medium">🌍 US = 43% of app traffic, 23 countries total. International word-of-mouth happening.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Acquisition -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Acquisition: Where Users Come From</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">56 visitors to the landing page. 155 to the app. The funnel is backwards: more people go straight to the app than discover it via the landing page.</p>

      <div class="space-y-2 mb-6">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/20 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <span class="text-amber-300 font-bold">ChatGPT</span>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-amber-300 font-mono">33 visitors</span>
            <span class="bg-amber-500/20 text-amber-300 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-sm font-bold">59%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <span class="text-gray-200 font-medium">Google</span>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-gray-300 font-mono">3 visitors</span>
            <span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">5%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <span class="text-gray-200 font-medium">Bing</span>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-gray-300 font-mono">3 visitors</span>
            <span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">5%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <span class="text-gray-200 font-medium">DuckDuckGo</span>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-gray-300 font-mono">2 visitors</span>
            <span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">4%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <span class="text-gray-200 font-medium">Direct</span>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-gray-300 font-mono">15 visitors</span>
            <span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">27%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-3">The ChatGPT Dominance</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">33 out of 56 landing visitors came from ChatGPT (27 with utm_source=chatgpt.com, 6 direct from chat.openai.com). That's 59% of all traffic.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3"><strong class="text-white">This is not SEO traffic.</strong> This is GEO: Generative Engine Optimization. Users are asking ChatGPT for calorie trackers, and it's recommending Chowdown.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6">The blog posts are working, but not through Google. They're getting indexed by LLMs and surfaced in conversational search. That's the game now.</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3">SEO is Underperforming</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6">Google: 3 visitors. Bing: 3. DuckDuckGo: 2. Combined, that's 8 visitors from traditional search in 30 days. The blog has 15+ posts. The /calculator page exists. The comparison content is live. But it's not ranking.</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3">Recommendations</h3>
      <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-bold mb-1">Double down on GEO, not SEO</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Write content optimized for LLM context windows: comparison posts, feature explainers, "best X for Y" listicles. Make it easy for ChatGPT to quote you.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-bold mb-1">Add schema markup to comparison posts</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Structured data helps LLMs extract facts. Add Product schema to "Chowdown vs X" posts with feature grids, pricing, and ratings.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-bold mb-1">Fix the landing page leak</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">71% bounce, 88 seconds average. People arrive from ChatGPT, read the headline, and leave. Add social proof, a demo video, and a clearer CTA above the fold.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-bold mb-1">Track ChatGPT mentions</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Set up monitoring for "Chowdown" + "calorie tracker" to see when ChatGPT or Perplexity surface the brand. Reverse-engineer which queries trigger mentions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Engagement -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Engagement: What Users Do</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">155 visitors, 888 pageviews, 274 visits. That's 5.7 pages per visitor and 1.8 visits per user. People are coming back.</p>

      <div class="space-y-2 mb-6">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <div>
            <span class="text-white font-bold">Food Logged</span>
            <p class="text-gray-400 text-xs mt-0.5">Core: 2.15 logs per active user</p>
          </div>
          <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono font-bold text-lg">333</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <div>
            <span class="text-white font-bold">Camera Opened</span>
            <p class="text-gray-400 text-xs mt-0.5">Photo input: 1:1 with visitors</p>
          </div>
          <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono font-bold text-lg">155</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <div>
            <span class="text-white font-bold">Text Chat Opened</span>
            <p class="text-gray-400 text-xs mt-0.5">Text logging nearly as popular as camera</p>
          </div>
          <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono font-bold text-lg">150</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <div>
            <span class="text-white font-bold">Badge Unlocked</span>
            <p class="text-gray-400 text-xs mt-0.5">58% of users engage with gamification</p>
          </div>
          <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono font-bold text-lg">90</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <div>
            <span class="text-white font-bold">Goal Updated</span>
            <p class="text-gray-400 text-xs mt-0.5">Users customise; not just browsing</p>
          </div>
          <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono font-bold text-lg">81</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <div>
            <span class="text-white font-bold">Signed In</span>
            <p class="text-gray-400 text-xs mt-0.5">19% sign-in rate. Barrier or feature?</p>
          </div>
          <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono font-bold text-lg">30</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3">Core Usage is Healthy</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">333 food logs across 155 users = 2.15 logs per person. That's not daily tracking (30+ logs), but it's not drive-by curiosity either. People are using it.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6">Camera: 155. Text chat: 150. Almost 50/50. Both entry methods matter. Don't over-optimise for one.</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3">Gamification is Working</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6">90 badges unlocked, but only 15 "Badges Tab Opened" events. Users are earning badges without actively seeking them. The notifications work; the discoverability doesn't.</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3">Social Features are Latent</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6">22 group views, 4 reactions. Groups exist, but engagement is low. Either users don't know about them, or the feature needs more surface area.</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3">Recommendations</h3>
      <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-blue-400 font-bold mb-1">Surface badge progress in the main UI</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">90 unlocks, 15 tab opens. Add a persistent "Next Badge: X logs away" widget on the home screen.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-blue-400 font-bold mb-1">Make groups more visible</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Promote during onboarding ("Join a community or track solo?"), or add a "Trending Groups" carousel.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-blue-400 font-bold mb-1">Test text-first onboarding</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Camera gets the headline, but text is just as popular. Try A/B testing "Type or snap" as the first prompt.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-blue-400 font-bold mb-1">Clarify the sign-in value prop</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Add a "Save your progress" prompt after the first food log. Don't force auth, but make the benefit clear.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Retention -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Retention Signals</h2>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-3 my-6">
        <div class="bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-black text-amber-400">39%</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">App Bounce</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-green-400 mt-1">✓ Good</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-black text-amber-400">4 min</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">Avg Session</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-green-400 mt-1">✓ Strong</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-black text-amber-400">1.8x</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">Visits/User</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-green-400 mt-1">↗ Growing</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">The product works. 39% bounce is healthy for a utility app. 4-minute sessions mean people are actually logging, not just peeking.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6">The problem is upstream. <strong class="text-white">71% of people who land on chowdown.me never make it to app.chowdown.me.</strong> That's the growth bottleneck.</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3">Recommendations</h3>
      <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-purple-400 font-bold mb-1">A/B test the landing page CTA</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Replace "Visit chowdown.me →" with "Try it now (no sign-up)" linking directly to app.chowdown.me.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-purple-400 font-bold mb-1">Add a "See it in action" video</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">A 30-second demo: photo → AI scan → macros. Converts fence-sitters who won't click through on text alone.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-purple-400 font-bold mb-1">Track cohort retention</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Set up Firebase Analytics cohorts for Day 1, Day 7, Day 30 retention. If Day 7 is above 20%, you're onto something.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Geographic -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Geographic Opportunity</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">155 app visitors from 23 countries.</p>

      <div class="space-y-2 mb-6">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/20 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <span class="text-amber-300 font-bold">🇺🇸 United States</span>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-amber-300 font-mono">67</span>
            <span class="bg-amber-500/20 text-amber-300 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-sm font-bold">43%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <span class="text-gray-200 font-medium">🇬🇧 United Kingdom</span>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-gray-300 font-mono">20</span>
            <span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">13%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <span class="text-gray-200 font-medium">🇸🇬 Singapore</span>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-gray-300 font-mono">10</span>
            <span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">6%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <span class="text-gray-200 font-medium">🇨🇭 Switzerland</span>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-gray-300 font-mono">8</span>
            <span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">5%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <span class="text-gray-200 font-medium">🇩🇪 Germany</span>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-gray-300 font-mono">7</span>
            <span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">5%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <span class="text-gray-200 font-medium">🌍 Other (18 countries)</span>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-gray-300 font-mono">43</span>
            <span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">28%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">US is the beachhead. 43% of app traffic, biggest fitness/nutrition app market. ChatGPT is recommending Chowdown to US users. Lean into it.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6">Lebanon (5), Peru (3), Malaysia (3): these aren't paid markets. This is organic word-of-mouth or LLM recommendations in non-English queries.</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3">Recommendations</h3>
      <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-orange-400 font-bold mb-1">US-specific landing variant</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Test with US units (oz, cups, lbs) and US-centric testimonials. 43% of traffic justifies localisation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-orange-400 font-bold mb-1">Multi-language blog posts</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">23 countries. Auto-translate top posts into Spanish, German, French via DeepL or GPT-4.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-orange-400 font-bold mb-1">Prioritise US influencers</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">When doing outreach, target US-based fitness creators first. The market is there.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Content Strategy -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Content &amp; Blog Strategy</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">15+ posts live. 3x/week publishing. But only 4 visits to the top blog post in 30 days.</p>

      <div class="space-y-2 mb-6">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <span class="text-gray-200 font-medium text-sm">best-free-calorie-counter-apps-2026</span>
          <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono font-bold">4 views</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <span class="text-gray-200 font-medium text-sm">/calculator</span>
          <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono font-bold">3 views</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <span class="text-gray-200 font-medium text-sm">/blog (directory)</span>
          <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono font-bold">3 views</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between bg-navy-800/50 border border-navy-700/50 rounded-lg px-4 py-3">
          <span class="text-gray-200 font-medium text-sm">carb-cycling-explained</span>
          <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono font-bold">2 views</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6">The blog isn't driving traffic yet. But it IS getting indexed by LLMs (the 27 utm_source=chatgpt.com visits prove it). The problem isn't quality; it's discoverability in traditional search.</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3">Recommendations</h3>
      <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <div class="border-l-4 border-pink-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-pink-400 font-bold mb-1">Write 5 comparison posts</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">"Chowdown vs MyFitnessPal", "vs Cronometer", "vs Lose It", "vs MacroFactor", "vs Lifesum". These rank better than generic "best X" posts and feed GEO momentum.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-pink-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-pink-400 font-bold mb-1">Cross-link the calculator page everywhere</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">3 visits to /calculator is criminal. Add a "Try the calculator" CTA at the end of every comparison post.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-pink-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-pink-400 font-bold mb-1">Syndicate to Medium, Dev.to, Hashnode</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Posts are already written. Republish with canonical tags to build backlinks and reach users where they read.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-pink-500 pl-4 py-2">
          <p class="text-pink-400 font-bold mb-1">Add "Recommended by ChatGPT" social proof</p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">59% of traffic from ChatGPT. That's a badge of honour. Use it on the landing page.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Product Roadmap -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Product Roadmap Priorities</h2>

      <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <div class="bg-red-500/10 border border-red-500/20 rounded-lg p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
            <span class="bg-red-500/20 text-red-400 w-7 h-7 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-mono text-sm font-bold">1</span>
            <span class="text-white font-bold">Landing Page Rewrite</span>
            <span class="bg-red-500/20 text-red-400 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-bold ml-auto">HIGH</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">71% bounce rate. Losing more than half your ChatGPT traffic before they see the app.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/20 rounded-lg p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
            <span class="bg-amber-500/20 text-amber-400 w-7 h-7 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-mono text-sm font-bold">2</span>
            <span class="text-white font-bold">Comparison Content Series</span>
            <span class="bg-red-500/20 text-red-400 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-bold ml-auto">HIGH</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">"Chowdown vs X" capitalises on GEO momentum. 5 posts in 10 days.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/20 rounded-lg p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
            <span class="bg-amber-500/20 text-amber-400 w-7 h-7 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-mono text-sm font-bold">3</span>
            <span class="text-white font-bold">Group Features Expansion</span>
            <span class="bg-amber-500/20 text-amber-400 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-bold ml-auto">MED</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">22 group views. Social aspect is latent but could drive retention and virality.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/20 rounded-lg p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
            <span class="bg-amber-500/20 text-amber-400 w-7 h-7 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-mono text-sm font-bold">4</span>
            <span class="text-white font-bold">Badge Progression Visibility</span>
            <span class="bg-amber-500/20 text-amber-400 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-bold ml-auto">MED</span>
          </div>
